41) Jade/Eleplant Bush/Portulacaria afra.  Jade is a succulent plant. It is considered really good in some communities, it is said that plant brings good fortune to their owners.  Plant needs - - - indirect or Artificial bright light is ideal  Water content - - - - soil should be well drained. Do not over  water the plant  Note  this that you have to water immediately after application of fertilizer.  For any insect attack.. Just spray neem oil.. That's enough. When in Reykjavik we highly recommend taking a late evening walk down to the sea side and along the old harbour, watching the sunset. The last few days have been sunny and we, the locals are enjoying the spring since we can go out and about as we like and most cafes and testaurants are open again. We hope it won’t be too long until you can enjoy all that Iceland has to offer with us again. Cairo, Egypt’s <U+0001F1EA><U+0001F1EC> sprawling capital, is set on the Nile River. At its heart is Tahrir Square and the vast Egyptian Museum, a trove of antiquities including royal mummies and gilded King Tutankhamun artifacts. Nearby, Giza is the site of the iconic pyramids and Great Sphinx, dating to the 26th century BC. In Gezira Island’s <U+0001F334> leafy Zamalek district, 187m Cairo Tower <U+0001F5FC> affords panoramic city views. . . Just outside the little and busy city of Flagstaff was the most gorgeous and secluded dispersed camping. We woke up the next morning with just under a hour drive to Sedona, as we drove through this beautiful state we could see the landscape change from desert and possibly the biggest Saguaros I have ever seen in person to big pine trees and then the brightest red rocks and sand I have ever stepped foot on! Pisa Tower. Italy Pisa got its name in 600 BC from a Greek word meaning “marshy land.” There are several other towers in Pisa that also lean: the bell tower at the church of St. Michele dei Scalzi, and the bell tower at the church of St. Nicola.The cathedral and baptistery are also sinking.  Galileo was baptized in the baptistery in 1565.  The foundation of the cemetery, Campo Santo, is made up of 53 shiploads of earth that were brought back from the Hill of Calvary in Jerusalem  The original completed height of the Tower of Pisa is 60 meters. Actually the tower’s height is 56.67m on the highest side and 55,86m on the lowest side.  The outside diameter of the leaning Tower of Pisa’s base is 15.484 meters.  #picofday<U+0001F4F7> #travelblog #travellersgram #traveldiary_aroundtheworld #pisaitaly #pisatower<U+0001F1EE><U+0001F1F9> #italytravel #italytrip #unescoheritagesites #unesco_world_heritage #heritagecity #passionpassports #leaningtower #visiteurope #exploreeurope #italylovers #architecturedaily #miracleshappeneveryday #squareofmiracles #exploreitaly #beautifuldesinations #earthofficial #passportready #earth_fantastics PC pld DM for credits
